    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen `bufpos` is set to a value outside the text of the buffer, the window is positioned oddly.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSave the following lua script, then open a clean Neovim and source it.\r\n```\r\nvim.api.nvim_open_win(vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true), 0, {\r\n  relative = \"win\",\r\n  width = 10,\r\n  height = 5,\r\n  bufpos = { 3, 3 },\r\n  row = 0,\r\n  col = 0,\r\n  style = \"minimal\",\r\n  border = \"single\"\r\n})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nEither an error because `bufpos` is out of range, or the window to appear in the top-left corner. Instead, the window appears in the bottom-left corner.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.10.0-dev-75+gc2e47e7be\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nRocky Linux 8.6\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nxfce4-terminal 1.0.4\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
